parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and other property.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without pressing the accelerator pedal
especially when coming to a stop or from a stop position

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Malfunction in Battery Fuse Box Area
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical malfunction in the battery fuse box area can cause a vehicle fire, resulting in significant damage or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle starts burning while parked and engine is not running

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Problems Causing Vehicle to Not Start
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical problems can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing inconvenience or safety risks.
Ignition coil failure can cause the vehicle to stall and not restart, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: secondary ignition coil wire gets severed
vehicle stalls and will not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Affecting Brake Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause brake lights to malfunction, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
The vehicle's sudden acceleration and brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal going to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the front brake rotors can cause vibration when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: repeated replacement of front brake rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can lead to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
